definition.value: A sulfoglycolipid in which alpha,alpha-trehalose, sulfated at the 2'-position, is acylated at the 2-position with palmitic acid, and at the 3-position with 2-methyloctadecanoic acid.
A sulfoglycolipid in which alpha,alpha-trehalose, sulfated at the 2'-position, is acylated at the 2-position with palmitic acid, and at the 3-position with (2S,4S)-2,4-dimethyldocosanoic acid.

A sulfoglycolipid in which alpha,alpha-trehalose, sulfated at the 2'-position, is acylated at the 2-position with palmitic acid, and at the 3-position with (2S,4S,6S)-2,4,6-trimethyltetracosanoic acid.
A methyl glycoside that is beta-D-galactopyranosyl-(1->4)-2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranose in which the anomeric hydroxy group is replaced by methoxy.

A sulfoglycolipid in which alpha,alpha-trehalose, sulfated at the 2'-position, is acylated at the 2-position with palmitic acid, and at the 3-position with (2S,4S,6S,8S)-2,4,6,8-tetramethyltetracosanoic acid.
A phosphocerebroside consisting of galactosylceramide having an N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine 1-phosphate moiety attached at the 6-position via a phosphodiester linkage.
A sulfoglycolipid in which alpha,alpha-trehalose, sulfated at the 2'-position, is acylated at the 2-position with palmitic acid, and at the 3-position with (2E)-2-methylicos-2-enoic acid.
A sulfoglycolipid in which alpha,alpha-trehalose, sulfated at the 2'-position, is acylated at the 2-position with palmitic acid, and at the 3-position with (2E,4S)-2,4-dimethyldocos-2-enoic acid.
A ceramide that consists of a cerebroside carrying one or more phosphate or alkyl phosphate substituents.

An amino tetrasaccharide comprising residues of galactose, N-acetylglucosamine, galactose and N-acetylglucosamine in a linear sequence, joined by beta-(1->4)-, beta-(1->3)-, and beta-(1->4)-linkages, respectively.

A sulfoglycolipid in which alpha,alpha-trehalose, sulfated at the 2'-position, is acylated at the 2-position with palmitic acid, and at the 3-position with (2E,4S,6S)-2,4,6-trimethyltetracos-2-enoic acid.
A glycosylmannose consisting of D-mannose having a beta-D-xylosyl residue attached at the 2-position.

A sulfoglycolipid in which alpha,alpha-trehalose, sulfated at the 2'-position, is acylated at the 2-position with palmitic acid, and at the 3-position with (2E,4S,6S,8S)-2,4,6,8-tetramethyltetracos-2-enoic acid.
A methyl glycoside that is beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc in which the anomeric hydroxy group is replaced by a beta-methoxy.

A sulfoglycolipid in which alpha,alpha-trehalose, sulfated at the 2'-position, is acylated at the 2-position with palmitic acid, and at the 3-position with (2E,4S,6S,8S,10S)-2,4,6,8,10-pentamethylhexacos-2-enoic acid.
A methyl glycoside derived from a hexasaccharide consisting of three units N-acetyllactosamine coupled in a linear sequence by beta-(1->3') linkages.

A sulfoglycolipid in which alpha,alpha-trehalose, sulfated at the 2'-position, is acylated at the 2-position with octanoic acid, and at the 3-position with (2E,4S,6S,8S)-2,4,6,8-tetramethylteracos-2-enoic acid.

A sulfoglycolipid in which alpha,alpha-trehalose, sulfated at the 2'-position, is acylated at the 2-position with tetracosanoic acid, and at the 3-position with (2E,4S,6S,8S)-2,4,6,8-tetramethyltetracos-2-enoic acid.
A sulfoglycolipid in which alpha,alpha-trehalose, sulfated at the 2'-position, is acylated at the 2-position with (2E,4S)-2,4-dimethyldocos-2-enoic acid, and at the 3-position with palmitoic acid.
A sulfoglycolipid in which alpha,alpha-trehalose, sulfated at the 2'-position, is acylated at the 2-position with palmitic acid, and at the 3-position with (2E,4R)-2,4-dimethyldocos-2-enoic acid.
An amino acid zwitterion arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of S-[(2E,6E)]-farnesyl-L-cysteine; major species at pH 7.3.
A tetrasaccharide consisting of two (1->5)-linked beta-D-galactofuranose units, which are in turn linked (1->6) to alpha-D-mannopyranosyl-(1->6)-D-mannopyranose.
A pentasaccharide composed of four (1->5)-linked beta-D-galactofuranose units, which are joined (1->6)-linkage to a D-mannopyranose at the reducing end.

A heptasaccharide derivative in which a backbone of one glucuronic acid, one 6-O-acetyl and three mannose residues is branched at each of the two non-terminal mannoses with a xylose residue, linked alpha(1->2).
A trisaccharide consisting of D-mannose at the reducing end having a beta-D-galactofuranosyl-(1->6)-alpha-D-mannosyl moiety attached at the 6-position.

An amino trisaccharide consisting of a 2-O-methyl-L-fucosyl residue at the non-reducing end linked (1->2) to an beta-D-galactosyl residue which is in turn linked (1->3) to an N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine.
A mannosyl group derived from (1->2)-beta-D-mannotetraose.

An amino trisaccharide consisting of a 2-O-methyl-L-fucosyl residue at the non-reducing end linked (1->2) to an beta-D-galactosyl residue which is in turn linked (1->3) to an N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosamine.
A disaccharide derivative consisting of a 2-O-methylfucosyl residue joined by an alpha-(1->2)-linkage to a 4-O-methyl-beta-D-galactose.
A member of the class of benzyl alcohols that is benzyl alcohol in which the hydrogens at positions 3 and 4 of the phenyl group are substituted by methoxy groups.
A mannosyl group derived from (1->2)-beta-D-mannopentaose.

An amino trisaccharide consisting of alpha-L-fucopyranose, beta-D-galactopyranose and N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactopyranosamine residues joined in sequence with a (1->2)- and a (1->3)-linkage, respectively.
A mannosyl group derived from (1->2)-beta-D-mannohexaose.

An amino trisaccharide consisting of alpha-L-fucopyranose, beta-D-galactopyranose and N-acetyl-beta-D-galactopyranosamine residues joined in sequence with a (1->2)- and a (1->3)-linkage, respectively; alpha-L-Fucp-(1->2)-beta-D-Galp-(1->3)-D-GalpNAc in which the configuration at the reducing-end anomeric centre is beta.
A glycosyl group derived from beta-D-mannopyranosyl-(1->2)-2-thio-beta-D-mannopyranosyl-(1->2)-2-thio-beta-D-mannopyranose
An amino trisaccharide consisting of two D-galactose residues, linked alpha(1->3), and an N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residue, linked alpha(1->4), at the reducing end.
A disaccharide derivative consisting of D-ribitol-5-phosphate having an alpha-L-rhamnosyl residue attached at the 4-position.
The trisaccharide beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-[beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->6)]-D-GalNAc with alpha configuration at the anomeric centre of the N-acetylglucosamine residue at the reducing end.

A disaccharide phosphate consisting of alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-alpha-D-glucose having a alpha-L-rhamnosyl-(1->4)-D-ribitol-5-phosphate moiety attached at the 2-position of the galactose via a phosphodiester linkage.
An amino trisaccharide in which two galactose residues, linked alpha(1->4), are linked beta(1->3) to an N-acetylgalactosamine residue.
A disaccharide phosphate consisting of alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-alpha-D-glucose having a D-ribitol-5-phosphate moiety attached at the 2-position of the galactose via a phosphodiester linkage.

An amino tetrasaccharide in which an N-acetylglucosamine residue is linked beta(1->6) to the residue at the reducing end of a linear chain of two galactose residues and an N-acetylglucosamine residue.
Any mannosamine carrying an N-acetyl substituent
An N-acetyl-D-mannosamine 6-phosphate having alpha-configuration at the anomeric centre.

A member of the class of ureas that is urea in which one of the nitrogens bears a 3-tert-butyl-1-(quinolin-6-yl)-1H-pyrazol-5-yl substituent, while the other bears a 2-fluoro-4-{[2-(methylcarbamoyl)pyridin-4-yl]oxy}phenyl substituent.
An L-arginine ester that is methyl L-argininate in which one of the hydrogens attached to the alpha-nitrogen is substituted by a tosyl group.
An N-acyl-D-mannosamine 6-phosphate having the N-acyl specified as acetyl.
An N-acyl-D-mannosamine phosphate having the phosphate group placed at the 6-position.
Any mannosamine phosphate having D-configuration and carrying an N-acyl substituent.
